2026-03-11 Gregor  <gregnix@github>
	* Bumped revision to 0.9.4.8
	* Fix ticket #2: /Length of content streams was systematically off
	  by one. In endPage, "incr data_len" was called before writing
	  "\nendstream\n", counting the preceding EOL toward /Length. Per
	  PDF spec §7.3.8.1 the end-of-line marker before "endstream" is
	  not part of the stream data and must not be included in /Length.
	  All PDFs produced by the fork had /Length too large by 1.
	  veraPDF reported rule 6.1.7 for every page stream. [#2]
	* Fix ticket #19: new option -pdfa (values "", "1b", "2b") enables
	  PDF/A conformance. When -pdfa is set, pdf4tcl automatically adds:
	  - XMP metadata stream with pdfaid identification schema
	    (pdfaid:part, pdfaid:conformance) required by ISO 19005-1 §6.7.11
	  - OutputIntent dictionary with sRGB ICC profile (/GTS_PDFA1)
	    required by ISO 19005-1 §6.2.2 and §6.2.3.3
	  - /Group /S /Transparency suppressed on all pages per
	    ISO 19005-1 §6.1.3 (no transparency in PDF/A-1)
	  New helper procs: _BuildXMPStream, _FindSRGBProfile,
	  _WriteOutputIntent. [#19]
	* New option -pdfa-icc: explicit path to sRGB ICC profile, used
	  when automatic search (_FindSRGBProfile) finds nothing.
	* validator: CheckPdfa accepts "", "1b", "2b"; rejects all other
	  values with a clear error message.

2026-03-10 pdf4tcl fork contributor

	* Fix: CID ToUnicode CMap -- SMP codepoints (U+10000..U+10FFFF) now
	  encoded as UTF-16BE surrogate pairs in bfchar entries per PDF spec
	  §9.10.3. Previously format "<%04X>" produced malformed 5-hex-digit
	  strings for SMP codepoints (e.g. <1F600> instead of <D83DDE00>).
	  PDF viewers and validators could not map SMP glyphs to Unicode.
	* util.test: new tests util-8.1..8.4 for SMP/surrogate encoding.


	  "A CMap has too many code maps" when PDF contains fonts with full
	  WinAnsi encoding. PDF spec §9.10.3 allows max 100 entries per
	  beginbfchar block. MakeToUnicodeCMap now writes chunked blocks.
	  [#24]
	* util.test: new tests util-7.1..7.3 for chunked beginbfchar.

2026-03-08 Gregor  <gregnix@github>
	* Bumped revision to 0.9.4.5
	* Feature ticket #16: new proc createFontSpecCID enables Unicode/CJK
	  support via CIDFontType2 (Identity-H encoding). Supports any script
	  covered by the TTF font (Latin Extended, Greek, Cyrillic, CJK, etc.)
	  without the 256-codepoint limit of createFontSpecEnc. [#16]
	* New proc CIDEncodeText: encodes Unicode strings as PDF hex strings
	  <GGGG...> using original GlyphIDs. Tracks used glyphs for W array.
	* New proc PdfText: unified text encoder routing to CIDEncodeText or
	  CleanText depending on font type. Replaces inline ([CleanText...])
	  at all ~13 text-rendering sites in main.tcl.
	* SetupFont: new "CID" branch defers font object writing to finish().
	  Font OID is reserved at SetupFont time; WriteCIDFontObjects writes
	  Type0 + CIDFontType2 + FontDescriptor + ToUnicode CMap at finish().
	* GetCharWidth: CID-aware: uses charToGlyph + hmetrics for widths.
	  getStringWidth and text-wrapping work correctly for CID fonts.
	* loadBaseTrueTypeFont / createBaseTrueTypeFont: now preserve the raw
	  TTF binary in BFP($bfname,rawttf) for CID embedding.
	* 26 new tests in tests/cidfont.test.
	* New demo: 0.9.4.x/demo/demo-cidfont.tcl.

